# Mobile Development Directory

This directory will contain mobile-specific configurations, scripts, and documentation for ThinkRank mobile app development.

## Structure

```
mobile/
├── react-native/          # React Native application
│   ├── src/              # Source code
│   ├── __tests__/        # Test files
│   ├── android/          # Android-specific files
│   ├── ios/              # iOS-specific files
│   └── package.json      # React Native dependencies
├── unity-integration/     # Unity integration modules
│   ├── bridges/          # React Native <-> Unity bridges
│   └── plugins/          # Unity plugins for mobile
├── scripts/              # Build and deployment scripts
│   ├── build-ios.sh      # iOS build script
│   ├── build-android.sh  # Android build script
│   └── deploy.sh         # Deployment automation
└── docs/                 # Mobile-specific documentation
    ├── setup.md          # Development environment setup
    ├── architecture.md   # Mobile architecture guide
    └── deployment.md     # Deployment procedures
```

## Getting Started

1. Follow the setup guide in `docs/setup.md`
2. Review the architecture documentation
3. Start with the React Native project setup

## Next Steps

This directory structure will be populated during the mobile development phase as outlined in the Mobile Development Strategy document.